  "response_text": "In the Heart of the Crowd, Alone\n\nAmidst the throng where lights aglow,\nA solitary soul does flow.\nIn the heart of the city's beat,\nWhere every face a story meets,\nI wander, lost in silent thought,\nA lone star in a sea of light.\n\nThe bustling streets, a constant hum,\nEchoes of laughter, distant drum,\nYet here, within my quiet mind,\nResides the echo of my kind.\nAlone, yet not unfeeling, I\nFind solace in the city's sigh.\n\nThe towering spires reach for the sky,\nGuarding secrets from the eye,\nWhile shadows dance upon the walls,\nOf buildings that seem to call.\nTo each one, a tale untold,\nIn their silence, I am bold.\n\nThe neon signs flicker and flash,\nA kaleidoscope of ashen glass,\nBut through it all, my gaze does rest,\nUpon the void where I am best.\nFor in this crowd, so vast",
